This is an Internal Chat + RAG application built with:
- React + Tailwind CSS + React Router (frontend)
- Express.js API server (backend, port 3001)
- Supabase (auth, realtime, storage, pgvector)
- OpenAI API (embeddings via text-embedding-3-small, chat completion)

Core architecture:
1. Real-time chat via Supabase Realtime subscriptions on the messages table
2. Document upload to Supabase Storage (documents bucket) with text extraction
3. Chunking + embedding generation pipeline (500 char chunks, 50 char overlap)
4. Vector similarity search via pgvector match_document_chunks() RPC
5. RAG response generation with source citations

Database tables:
- channels: Chat channels with optional AI-enabled flag
- messages: Chat messages with optional RAG source references
- documents: Uploaded document metadata
- document_chunks: Chunked text with vector embeddings (1536-dim)

When extending this app:
- Preserve the RAG pipeline (upload -> chunk -> embed -> search -> generate)
- Use Supabase Realtime for any new real-time features
- Keep the channel-based chat structure
- Add new document types by extending the chunker
- Industry-specific features should be added as new pages/modules
- All API calls go through the Express server via /api/ proxy
- Environment variables: VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY
